{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "As with the number of attention heads, the number of decoder layers is a hyperparameter.",
    "Too few layers can diminish a model's capacity for learning complex rules but too many layers can increase the risk of overfitting, which spoils the model's ability to generalize.",
    "Intuition: Each decoder layer makes further adjustments to the contextual representation of tokens based on learning something different about how tokens in the sequence influence each other to express meaning.",
    "The contextualized meanings of current tokens may change as the decoder predicts future tokens.",
    "Researchers demonstrated that downstream decoder layers gradually express global (deeper) dependencies versus local (shallow) dependencies among tokens (Geva et al. 2020)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Researchers demonstrated that downstream decoder layers gradually express global (deeper) dependencies versus local (shallow) dependencies among tokens (Geva et al. 2020)."
  ]
}